The acclimated biofilm was dispersed in saline solution (3% NaCl, 34.2 mM phosphate buffer pH 7.4), and serial dilutions were made and inoculated onto the Methylophaga medium 1403 (American Type Culture Collection [ATCC], Manassas, VA, USA) supplemented with 1.5% agar and 0.3% v/v methanol. The plates were incubated at 30 °C for no more than 7 days, under oxic conditions (no NO\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
